{
  "uid": "panol-logs",
  "title": "Pañol IoT — logs en vivo",
  "description": "Logs de todos los contenedores del host + escrituras en la base del pañol. Los logs solo responden con el stack `logs` prendido (make logs-on): está apagado por defecto a propósito.",
  "tags": [
    "panol",
    "logs",
    "tiempo real"
  ],
  "timezone": "America/Argentina/Buenos_Aires",
  "editable": true,
  "schemaVersion": 39,
  "version": 1,
  "refresh": "10s",
  "time": {
    "from": "now-15m",
    "to": "now"
  },
  "templating": {
    "list": [
      {
        "name": "stack",
        "label": "Stack",
        "type": "query",
        "datasource": {
          "type": "loki",
          "uid": "loki"
        },
        "query": "label_values(stack)",
        "refresh": 2,
        "includeAll": true,
        "multi": true,
        "current": {
          "text": "panol",
          "value": "panol"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "contenedor",
        "label": "Contenedor",
        "type": "query",
        "datasource": {
          "type": "loki",
          "uid": "loki"
        },
        "query": "label_values({stack=~\"$stack\"}, contenedor)",
        "refresh": 2,
        "includeAll": true,
        "multi": true,
        "current": {
          "text": "All",
          "value": "$__all"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "buscar",
        "label": "Buscar texto",
        "type": "textbox",
        "query": "",
        "current": {
          "text": "",
          "value": ""
        }
      }
    ]
  },
  "panels": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "Cómo se prende (y por qué está apagado)",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 4,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "Indexar los logs de todos los contenedores cuesta RAM, CPU y disco **todo el tiempo**, y este servidor también corre el laboratorio del aula. Por eso el stack de logs vive apagado.\n\nEn el servidor: `logs-en-vivo` (o `make logs-on` desde el repo). Pregunta cada 5 minutos si seguir y **se apaga solo** si no contestás — también si cerrás la terminal.\n\nSi los paneles de abajo dicen *connection refused*, está apagado: no es un error de configuración. Los paneles de la base, en cambio, andan siempre."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "type": "logs",
      "title": "Logs — $stack / $contenedor",
      "description": "Todos los contenedores del host, filtrables. Elegí 'All' en Stack para ver el servidor entero.",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 13,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 4
      },
      "datasource": {
        "type": "loki",
        "uid": "loki"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "{stack=~\"$stack\", contenedor=~\"$contenedor\"} |= \"$buscar\"",
          "queryType": "range",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "loki",
            "uid": "loki"
          }
        }
      ],
      "options": {
        "showTime": true,
        "showLabels": true,
        "showCommonLabels": true,
        "wrapLogMessage": true,
        "prettifyLogMessage": false,
        "enableLogDetails": true,
        "dedupStrategy": "none",
        "sortOrder": "Ascending"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Escrituras en la base, por tabla",
      "description": "Cada barra es una fila nueva en la auditoría. Esto sí anda siempre: sale de Postgres, no de Loki.",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 17
      },
      "datasource": {
        "type": "postgres",
        "uid": "panol-postgres"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "format": "time_series",
          "rawQuery": true,
          "rawSql": "SELECT $__timeGroupAlias(t, '1m', 0), tabla AS metric, count(*) AS value FROM (SELECT timestamp AS t, 'accesos' AS tabla FROM eventos_acceso WHERE $__timeFilter(timestamp) UNION ALL SELECT timestamp, 'puerta' FROM eventos_puerta WHERE $__timeFilter(timestamp) UNION ALL SELECT timestamp, 'pir' FROM eventos_pir WHERE $__timeFilter(timestamp) UNION ALL SELECT timestamp, 'alarmas' FROM alarmas WHERE $__timeFilter(timestamp)) x GROUP BY 1, 2 ORDER BY 1",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "postgres",
            "uid": "panol-postgres"
          }
        }
      ],
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "displayMode": "list",
          "placement": "bottom",
          "showLegend": true,
          "calcs": []
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi",
          "sort": "none"
        }
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "drawStyle": "bars",
            "fillOpacity": 70,
            "lineWidth": 1,
            "stacking": {
              "mode": "normal",
              "group": "A"
            }
          },
          "min": 0
        },
        "overrides": [
          {
            "matcher": {
              "id": "byName",
              "options": "alarmas"
            },
            "properties": [
              {
                "id": "color",
                "value": {
                  "mode": "fixed",
                  "fixedColor": "red"
                }
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "timeFrom": "24h"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "type": "table",
      "title": "Lo último que entró a la base",
      "description": "Feed unificado de las cuatro tablas de eventos, lo más nuevo arriba.",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 12,
        "y": 17
      },
      "datasource": {
        "type": "postgres",
        "uid": "panol-postgres"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "format": "table",
          "rawQuery": true,
          "rawSql": "SELECT t AS hora, tabla, ubicacion, detalle FROM (SELECT timestamp AS t, 'acceso' AS tabla, ubicacion_id AS ubicacion, uid_hex || ' → ' || resultado AS detalle FROM eventos_acceso WHERE $__timeFilter(timestamp) UNION ALL SELECT timestamp, 'puerta', ubicacion_id, estado_reed FROM eventos_puerta WHERE $__timeFilter(timestamp) UNION ALL SELECT timestamp, 'pir', ubicacion_id, 'movimiento' FROM eventos_pir WHERE $__timeFilter(timestamp) UNION ALL SELECT timestamp, 'ALARMA', ubicacion_id, codigo || ' (' || severidad || ')' FROM alarmas WHERE $__timeFilter(timestamp)) x ORDER BY t DESC LIMIT 100",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "postgres",
            "uid": "panol-postgres"
          }
        }
      ],
      "options": {
        "showHeader": true,
        "cellHeight": "sm",
        "footer": {
          "show": false
        }
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "align": "auto",
            "filterable": true
          }
        },
        "overrides": [
          {
            "matcher": {
              "id": "byName",
              "options": "tabla"
            },
            "properties": [
              {
                "id": "custom.cellOptions",
                "value": {
                  "type": "color-text"
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "mappings",
                "value": [
                  {
                    "type": "value",
                    "options": {
                      "ALARMA": {
                        "color": "red",
                        "index": 0
                      },
                      "acceso": {
                        "color": "green",
                        "index": 1
                      },
                      "puerta": {
                        "color": "blue",
                        "index": 2
                      },
                      "pir": {
                        "color": "text",
                        "index": 3
                      }
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "timeFrom": "24h"
    }
  ]
}